We have a system that has a list of company wide users. Unfortunately, it doesn't use standard field separators in the parameters in the URL, but uses ',' instead. Unfortunately, Confluence escapes this.

For example:
{{http://www.example.com/test?foo=%s,bar=1,baz=2}}

is expanding to 
{{http://www.example.com/test?foo%3Dwibble%2Cbar%3D1%2Cbaz%3D2}}

With the argument of "wibble".

The expected output is:
{{http://www.example.com/test?foo=wibble,bar=1,baz=2}}


Confluence should ideally not escape other characters and should allow the administrator to escape them if they want to.

