The templates in Confluence are powerful, especially because they can be generated at both the space level as well as the global level. However, we now have many spaces (100+) with various uses. Say that for several types of spaces you would like to reuse a template, a global template does this. But adding it as a global template has the disadvantage the template also becomes visible to spaces for which it is not relevant, some users get confused if they see to many (global) template options.

Is it possible to have an option to tick off for which spaces the global template should be made available?

