It would be nice to set a starting page for live-search. So if you have a project live-search will list only the pages which belongs to this project, not all pages in the whole space.

e.g.
{live-search:id=1|parent=project1}

With this option, live-search will only search (and display) all pages under _"project1"_

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-13957].
  {panel}

The steps to reproduce:
# Create a page which contains the following URL address:
{noformat}
http://example.com/?param={test}%20-%20two%20problems%20with%20that:%20{test}
{noformat}
# Save the page

Confluence will render the page as the attached file.

The revamped jiraissues macro in 2.10 is breaking layouts that use columns. When a jiraissues macro is embedded in a page column:

{section}
{column:width=50%}
First column
{jiraissues:url=http://test.jira.com/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest-xml/temp/SearchRequest.xml?pid=10226&sorter/field=issuekey&sorter/order=DESC&tempMax=1000}
{column}
{column}
A second column
{column}
{section}

The jiraissues macro in 2.9.2 used to do its best to fix within the given constraints.

In Confluence 2.10, the jiraissues macro grabs as much page width as it can, pushing the second column off the screen.  If the window is resized to include both the (huge) jiraissues and the second column, and refreshed, the jiraissues macro grabs still more space, pushing the second column off the screen again.

